Joyce Tabram was admitted to Fiona Stanley Hospital in Perth on March 30 with a swollen abdomen . 
  She was told to fast for five days while waiting for tests to be performed . 
  Ms Tabram lost five kilograms in five days at the hospital . 
  The 82-year-old was 39 kilograms when she was admitted . 
  Health Minister Kim Hames said she had a medical condition that required her to fast and was given fluids intravenously . 
  She arrived at hospital with swollen abdomen but left weighing just 34 kilograms . 
 